programme.title: Ainsley's Food We Love
programme.desc: Join Ainsley in the kitchen, as he is inspired by winter warming dishes. The nights are getting longer, and so we seek for those comfort dishes to keep us warm and toasty! programme.title: Asia Unplated
programme.desc: Singaporean cuisine is widely influenced by several ethnic groups that make up the population. programme.desc: Karena and Kasey head to Seoul, home to one of the most popular and on trend cuisines in the world. - After meeting the Kiwi Ambassador, Karena and Kasey are taken out to try traditional Korean BBQ and a sing along with a Korean, Kiwi twist. - The sisters then split up—one heads to the hills and has a lesson with a kimchi Master, while the other eats her way around the famous Gwangjang Market. - At the end of the week they showcase Kiwi-Korean fusion cuisine to an elite group of foodies.
